creator: Jules Verne
description:
LibriVox recording of Celebrated Travels and Travellers, vol. 3 by Jules Verne. (Translated by N. D'Anvers.)
Read in English by Ed Villines; Piotr Nater; MaryAnn; Jairus Amar; Michele Fry; Availle; Barbara Baker; Larry Wilson; ismailuser55; Richard Aroksaar; TriciaG
This volume, entitled "The great explorers of the 19th century", forms the third of three volumes under the general title of "Celebrated travels and travellers".

Volume three comprehends:
"The dawn of a century of discovery" (part I, chap. I), "The exploration and colonization of Africa" (part I, chap. II), "The oriental scientific movement and American discoveries" (part I, chap. III), "Voyages round the world, and Polar expeditions" (part II, chap. I), "French circumnavigators" (part II, chap. II), "Polar expeditions" (part II, chap. III, part I) and "The North Pole" (part II, chap. III, part II). - Summary by Kajo


For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
